LOCAL
CIRCUMFERENTIAL
BUCKLING
OF
THIN
CIRCULAR
CYLINDRICAL
SHELLS
THE
PROBLEM
OF
CIRCUMFERENTIAL
BUCKLING
OF
A
THIN
CIRCULAR
CYLINDRICAL
SHELL
DUE
TO
COMPRESSIVE
HOOP
STRESSES
WHICH
VARY
IN
THE
AXIAL
DIRECTION
IS
EXAMINED
FOR
EXTREMELY
LOCALISED
COMPRESSIVE
HOOP
STRESS
DISTRIBUTIONS
RESULTING
FROM
THERMAL
DISCONTINUITY
EFFECTS
OR
FROM
A
UNIFORM
RADIAL
LINE
LOADING
THE
BUCKLE
PATTERN
SHOULD
ALSO
BE
LOCALISED
SIMPLIFIED
ANALYSES
INTO
THESE
TWO
TYPES
OF
PROBLEM
ARE
CONSIDERED
WHICH
SHOW
THAT
ONLY
A
LIMITED
NUMBER
OF
BUCKLE
DEFLECTION
MODES
NEEDS
TO
BE
ASSUMED
